Defendant Nathanial A Froiland in court with attorney Anthony D Cotton.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State filed an Amended Information.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the Defense.  Statement by defendant's father.  Statement by defendant.

Court orders the following:
- Total sentence: 10 years (Initial Confinement: 5 years, Extended Supervision: 5 years) STAYED.  Credit for 1 day if revoked.
- 4 years Probation. 
- Court costs of $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
- Conditions of Probation:  No contact with minors outside of incidental contact through employment.  No use of internet to engage in chat rooms, dating sites, Craig's list, etc.  Sex offender treatment - Court would approve defendant continuing treatment at Pathways.
CONDITION TIME: 6 months - NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence August 3, 2015 by 12:00 pm.  Defendant may serve condition time in Milwaukee County.  Defendant may petition the Court for Day Reporting after 3 months.
